[{"location":"examples/turing/#Fitting-zero-inflated-models-using-Turing.jl","page":"Examples","title":"Fitting zero-inflated models using Turing.jl","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/turing/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"This example shows how you can use ZeroInflation.jl to fit zero-inflated models using Turing.jl. ","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/turing/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"First we need to create some sample data. In this example we will use a simple zero-inflated Poisson model with parameter \\lambda = 5.0 and mixing probability p = 0.25 and create 2000 samples from this distribution","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/turing/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"using Distributions, ZeroInflation\n\nlambda = 5.0\np = 0.25\n\nzero_inflated_poisson = zeroinflated(Poisson(lambda), p)\nsamp = rand(zero_inflated_poisson, 2_000)","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/turing/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"In a next step we create a Turing model assuming a a true prior on the Poisson parameter lambda and a flat Beta prior in the mixing probability. Then we fit the model to our sampled data samp.","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/turing/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"using Turing\n\n@model function ZIPoisson(y)\n    lambda ~ truncated(Normal(5.0, 1.0), 0, Inf)\n    p ~ Beta(1, 1)\n    \n    for n in 1:length(y)\n        y[n] ~ zeroinflated(Poisson(lambda), p)\n    end\nend\n\nmodel = ZIPoisson(samp)\nchain = sample(model, NUTS(0.65), 2_000)","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"CurrentModule = ZeroInflation","category":"page"},{"location":"#ZeroInflation","page":"Home","title":"ZeroInflation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Documentation for ZeroInflation.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Modules = [ZeroInflation]","category":"page"}]
